I've been experimenting, and it doesn't appear for it to be possible to specify a recursive proof as public input. The following syntax does not compile:

```
export const CoordinatesInPolygon = Experimental.ZkProgram({
    publicOutput: CoordinateInPolygonCommitment,
    publicInput: Proof<Empty, NoncedGeographicalPoint>, // ISSUE HERE

    methods: {...}
...
}
```

I looked through the source code and the public input/output only accept Pure values, which leads me to believe that they can't be recursive proofs.

Consider the following ZKPrograms:

```
class InnerProofPublicInput extends Struct({
    a: Field,
    b: Field,
}) { }

class InnerProofPublicOutput extends Struct({
    a: Field,
    b: Field,
}) { }

export const Inner = Experimental.ZkProgram({
    publicInput: InnerProofPublicInput, 
    publicOutput: InnerProofPublicOutput,

    methods: {
        innerProofMethod: {
            privateInputs: [],
            method: (pubilcInput: InnerProofPublicInput) => {
                return new InnerProofPublicOutput({a: Field(0), b: Field(1)});
            },
        },
    }
});

export const UnusedInner = Experimental.ZkProgram({
    publicInput: InnerProofPublicInput, 
    publicOutput: InnerProofPublicOutput,

    methods: {
        innerProofMethod: {
            privateInputs: [],
            method: (pubilcInput: InnerProofPublicInput) => {
                return new InnerProofPublicOutput({a: Field(10), b: Field(20)});
            },
        },
    }
});

export const Outer = Experimental.ZkProgram({
    publicInput: Empty, 
    publicOutput: Bool,

    methods: {
        outerProofMethod: {
            privateInputs: [SelfProof<InnerProofPublicInput, InnerProofPublicOutput>],
            method: (innerProof: SelfProof<InnerProofPublicInput, InnerProofPublicOutput>) => {
                innerProof.verify();
                const result: Bool = Provable.if(innerProof.publicOutput.a.equals(Field(0)), Bool(true), Bool(false));
                return result;
            },
        },
    }
});

const innerProof = await Inner.innerProofMethod(new InnerProofPublicInput({a: Field(100), b: Field(200)}));
const outerProof = await Outer.outerProofMethod(innerProof);
```
